{{more citations needed|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox video game |title = Age of Wonders II: The Wizard's Throne | image = Age of Wonders II - The Wizard's Throne Coverart.png |caption = |developer = [[Triumph Studios]] |publisher = [[Gathering of Developers]] |designer = Lennart Sas |producer = Chris Lacey |composer = [[Mason B. Fisher]] |engine = |released = {{vgrelease|NA|June 12, 2002<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/pc/459432-age-of-wonders-ii-the-wizards-throne/data|title= Age of Wonders II: The Wizard's Throne |publisher=[[GameFAQs]]|date= |accessdate=}}</ref>|EU|September 20, 2002}} |genre = [[Turn-based strategy]] |modes = [[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]] }}
'''''Age of Wonders II: The Wizard's Throne''''' is a [[turn-based strategy]] [[video game]] in a [[fantasy]] setting. The sequel to ''[[Age of Wonders]]'', it was developed by [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[video game developer]] [[Triumph Studios]].
==Gameplay== Unlike in ''Age of Wonders'', where the player has the option of removing their leader from the map, players in ''Age of Wonders II'' take the role of an immortal spell-casting Wizard, who cannot be upgraded, but in certain circumstances can survive being killed.
[[Image:Age of Wonder 2 screencap2.jpg|thumb|left|Screen capture of tactical battle in ''Age of Wonders II''.]]
===Combat and heroes=== In contrast to ''Age of Wonders'', the maps for tactical battles are now much smaller. This led to faster [[combat]] and less maneuvering of units. Also in contrast to its predecessor, when gaining new levels Heroes can no longer choose new skills from a list of all available skills; instead, the player is forced to choose one of three offered skills, depending on the Hero's class.
===Magic system=== In ''Age of Wonders'', magic is used via the spell casting abilities of leaders and heroes, and global spells can be cast some distance away from the hero; use of spells in combat is restricted to battles where a hero with spell casting is present.
Magic use in ''Age of Wonders II'' uses a "domain" system; spells can only be cast within the domain of the casting wizard, or the domain of an allied wizard. Magic domains can overlap with each other, and in the simple case, are centered <!-- do '''not''' change this to "centered" - check Wiktionary --> on the Wizard. When a Wizard is present in a Wizard's Tower, the radius of the domain increases significantly, and in addition is radiated by other Wizard's Towers, Magic Relays and Heroes under the control of the player. Global spells can only be cast by the Wizard, via a spell book located in the main user interface; spells can be cast in combat by either Heroes involved in the battle, or (provided the battle takes place inside their domain) the Wizard who controls any party which entered the battle.
[[Image:Age of Wonder 2 screencap1.jpg|thumb|right|A war party preparing to attack a city defended by Nimue.]]
==Development== {{empty-section|date=April 2018}}
==Reception== {{Video game reviews | CGW = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=cgw>{{cite journal| author=McDonald, Thomas L. |title=''Age of Wonders II: The Wizard's Throne'' |date=September 2002 | journal=[[Computer Gaming World]]|issue=218 |pages=86, 87 }}</ref> | GI = 8.5 out of 10<ref name=gi>{{cite journal | author=Brogger, Kristian; McNamara, Andy | journal=[[Game Informer]] | url=http://www.gameinformer.com/Games/Review/200208/R03.0801.1645.27201.htm| | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090811064054/http://www.gameinformer.com/Games/Review/200208/R03.0801.1645.27201.htm| archivedate=August 11, 2009 | title=Strategy for Your Inner Nerd | deadurl=yes | df= }}</ref> | PCZone = 82/100<ref name=pczone>{{cite journal| title=''Age of Wonders II: The Wizard's Throne'' | author=Anderson, Chris | journal=[[PC Zone]] | deadurl= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081202185250/http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=77855 | url=http://www.computerandvideogames.com/article.php?id=77855 | date=August 4, 2002| archivedate=December 2, 2008 }}</ref> | PCGUS = 90%<ref name=pcgamerus>{{cite journal | author=Trotter, William R. | journal=[[PC Gamer US]] | url=http://www.pcgamer.com/archives/2005/06/age_of_wonders_1.html | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080213025859/http://www.pcgamer.com/archives/2005/06/age_of_wonders_1.html | archivedate=February 13, 2008 | title=''Age of Wonders II'' | deadurl=yes | df= }}</ref>
}}
Improved audio quality and graphics, sub-quests from various gods, more races and build options as well as two large single-player campaigns made most of the large fanbase of ''[[Age of Wonders]]'' happy migrating to ''Age of Wonders II: The Wizard's Throne''{{citation needed|date=June 2014}}; this was aided by the involvement of members of the HeavenGames community in suggestions, testing and development of the game.{{citation needed|date=October 2017}}
Probably planned as an [[expansion pack]], ''[[Age of Wonders: Shadow Magic]]'' was published later as a stand-alone game.{{citation needed|date=October 2017}}
''Age of Wonders II'' was a nominee for ''[[PC Gamer US]]''{{'}}s "2002 Best Turn-Based Strategy Game" award, which ultimately went to ''[[Combat Mission: Barbarossa to Berlin]]''.<ref name=pcgamerusawards2003>{{cite journal |date=March 2003 | title=The Ninth Annual ''PC Gamer'' Awards | volume=10 | number=3 | pages=48–50, 54, 58, 60, 66, 68, 70 | journal=[[PC Gamer US]] | author=Staff }}</ref> It was also a finalist for ''[[EP Daily|The Electric Playground]]''{{'}}s 2002 "Best Strategy Game for PC" prize, but lost to ''[[Warcraft III: Reign of Chaos]]''.<ref name=blister2002>{{cite web | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20030308163735/http://elecplay.com/feature.html?article=10626#mr_toppy | url=http://elecplay.com:80/feature.html?article=10626#mr_toppy | title=Blister Awards 2002 | archivedate=2003-03-08 | author=Staff | work=[[EP Daily|The Electric Playground]] | deadurl=yes | access-date=2018-10-04 | df= }}</ref>
