{{unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox video game| title = Armored Core: Nexus |image = Sep line01.gif.jpg |caption = North American cover art |developer = [[FromSoftware]] |publisher = [[Agetec]]{{vgrelease|JP|FromSoftware}} |director = Rintaro Yamada |producer = Toshifumi Nabeshima |designer = |writer = |programmer = Ryoutarou Kishi |artist = |composer = [[Kota Hoshino]] |engine = |series = ''[[Armored Core]]'' |released = {{Vgrelease|JP|March 18, 2004|NA|September 28, 2004|EU|April 13, 2006}} |genre = [[Action game|Action]], [[third-person shooter]] |modes = [[Single player video game|Single player]], [[multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] |platforms = [[PlayStation 2]] }} '''''Armored Core: Nexus''''' is a [[mecha]] video game in the ''[[Armored Core]]'' series, developed by [[FromSoftware]] and published by [[Agetec]]. It is the sequel to ''[[Silent Line: Armored Core]]''.{{Citation needed|date=October 2015}}
==Plot== Years have passed since [[Silent Line: Armored Core|the incident at the Silent Line]], and with it the collaborative effort began by the Corporations in response to it is long gone. The battle between the Corporations has re-emerged and continues unabated. Now a new Corporation has entered the scene; this Corporation, Navis, while nowhere near the size of the other Corporations, does have a trump card; it has complete control over a brand new and very useful resource, and they do not intend to share. The other Corporations obviously will not sit back and let that stand, so they set up contracts with Ravens through Raven's Ark. Of course, Navis is employing the use of the Ravens as well, and a full-scale conflict seems apparent on the horizon.
