{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{Infobox company |name=Black Element Software |logo=Black Element Software logo.png |type = [[Subsidiary]] |parent = [[Bohemia Interactive]] |slogan= |foundation= 2000 |location= [[Prague]], [[Czech Republic]] |key_people= |num_employees= |industry=[[Video game development]] |revenue= |homepage={{URL|http://www.blackelement.net/}} |products=''[[Shade: Wrath of Angels]]'', ''[[Alpha Prime]]'' }}
'''Black Element Software Co., LTD''' is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[video game developer]] based in [[Prague]], [[Czech Republic]]. Prior to their acquisition by [[Bohemia Interactive Studio]] in 2010, they [[video game developer|developed]] [[Video game|computer and console]] games directly.
==History== Black Element Software was founded in 2000 by the members of Insanity, known for their games [[Testament (video game)|Testament]] and [[Testament II]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Testament II|url=http://hol.abime.net/5739|website=Hall of Light|accessdate=2 July 2014}}</ref> They released their first game, ''[[Shade: Wrath of Angels]]'', on 1 October 2004. In 2005, they joined with [[Bohemia Interactive Studio]] and [[Altar Games]] to form IDEA Games, which functioned as a publisher and consultant for several independent developers.<ref>{{cite web|title=IDEA Games|url=http://www.giantbomb.com/idea-games/3010-488/|website=Giant Bomb|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref>
On 30 September 2010, Black Element Software was acquired by fellow IDEA Games member [[Bohemia Interactive]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idea-games.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=165&Itemid=2 |title=Support |publisher=Idea Games |date= |accessdate=15 August 2013}}</ref> Despite this acquisition, [[Bohemia Interactive]] promised that the acquired companies, including Black Element Software, would continue to operate individually.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bistudio.com/index.php/english/company/profile |title=Bohemia Interactive company profile |publisher=Bistudio.com |date= |accessdate=15 August 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130811154953/http://www.bistudio.com/index.php/english/company/profile |archivedate=11 August 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Since acquisition, Black Element Software has been credited as a subsidiary of Bohemia Interactive Studio.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zing.cz/special/974/bohemia-interactive-studio-ktere-zlepsilo-herni-prumysl-kapitola-sesta-arma-2-se-rozsiruje |title=Speciál: Bohemia Interactive: Studio, které zlepšilo herní průmysl - Kapitola šestá - Arma 2 se rozšiřuje|language=Czech |publisher=Zing.cz |date= |accessdate=15 August 2013}}</ref>
As of 2014, Black Element Software now provides 3D modeling and related services for other game developers.<ref>{{cite web|title=Official Website|url=http://blackelement.net/|website=Black Element Software|accessdate=22 October 2015}}</ref>
==Games/expansion packs== *''[[Shade: Wrath of Angels]]'' (Windows) - 1 October 2004 (EU) / 14 October 2004 (NA) *''[[Alpha Prime]]'' (Windows) - 25 May 2007 (EU) / 8 November 2007 (NA) *''[[ARMA: Queen's Gambit|ArmA: Queen's Gambit]]'' (Windows) - 28 September 2007 (WW)
== Games released under Bohemia Interactive Studio == *''[[Carrier Command: Gaea Mission]]'' (PC, Xbox 360, PS3) - 28 September 2012 (WW)
