==Draft==
Starting in 2007, the Globetrotters have conducted an annual "draft" a few days before the [[National Basketball Association Draft|NBA draft]], in which they select players they feel fit the mold of a Globetrotter. Being drafted by the Globetrotters does not guarantee a spot on the team, although several drafted players have gone on to become Globetrotters: Anthony "Ant" Atkinson (2007), Brent Petway (2007), William "Bull" Bullard (2008), Tay "Firefly" Fisher (2008), Charlie Coley III (2009), Paul "Tiny" Sturgess (2011), Jacob "Hops" Tucker (2011), Darnell "Spider" Wilks (2011), Bryan "B-Nice" Narcisse (2012), Tyrone Davis (2013), Corey "Thunder" Law (2013), Tyler "Iceman" Inman (2014) Devan "Beast" Douglas (2016) and AJ "Money" Merriweather.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.harlemglobetrotters.com/news/harlem-globetrotters-mark-10th-anniversary-draft-first-ever-live-announcements-twitter|title=Harlem Globetrotters Mark 10th Anniversary of Draft with First-Ever Live Announcements on Twitter|date=29 July 2016|publisher=}}</ref>

Other notable draft picks by the Globetrotters include: [[Sun Mingming]] (2007), [[Patrick Ewing, Jr.]] (2008), [[Sonny Weems]] (2008), [[Taylor Griffin]] (2009), [[Tim Howard]] (2009), [[Mark Titus]] (2010), [[Lionel Messi]] (2011), [[Andrew Goudelock]] (2011), [[Usain Bolt]] (2012), [[Mariano Rivera]] (2013), [[Brittney Griner]] (2013), [[Johnny Manziel]] (2014), [[Landon Donovan]] (2014), [[Mo'ne Davis]] (2015), [[Dude Perfect]] (2015), [[Neymar]] (2016), [[Missy Franklin]] (2016), [[Jordan Spieth]] (2016), [[Craig Sager]] (2016), [[Gal Gadot]] (2017), [[Aaron Judge]] (2017), [[Tim Tebow]] (2017) [[Paul Pogba]] (2018), and [[Joseph Kilgore]] (2018).<ref name=Draft>{{cite news| first= Patrick |last= Dorsey | url= http://sports.espn.go.com/espn/page2/story?page=dorsey-110623_lionel_messi_globetrotters |title= A brief history of the Harlem Globetrotters' draft picks, including Lionel Messi| website= [[ESPN]].com| date= 2011-07-23| access-date= 2012-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url= http://espn.go.com/blog/cleveland-browns/post/_/id/6273/three-sports-harlem-globetrotters-draft-manziel| title= Three sports: Globetrotters draft Manziel| first= Pat| last= McManamon| website= ESPN.com|publisher=ESPN Inc.| date= June 24, 2014| access-date= July 28, 2016}}</ref><ref name=Griner>{{cite news| first= Kate |last= Fagan| url= http://espn.go.com/wnba/story/_/id/9421631/brittney-griner-harlem-globetrotters-thanks-no-thanks| title= Griner turns down Globetrotters| website= ESPN.com |publisher=ESPN Inc. |date= 2013-06-25| access-date= 2013-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.harlemglobetrotters.com/news/2017-player-draft|title=2017 Player Draft|date=2017-06-20|work=Harlem Globetrotters|access-date=July 6, 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.harlemglobetrotters.com/news/announcing-2018-harlem-globetrotter-draftees| title= Announcing the 2018 Harlem Globetrotter Draftees!| date =2018-06-19| work=Harlem Globetrotters| access-date=June 19, 2018|language=en}}</ref>

